{"title": "Science Is Good", "content": "\"Truth is binary. There is one, positive, yes, light, the machine, progress, upgrade, holism, independence, eternity. And there is the opposite of these, which is anathema.\"\n\nThe Inverted Trope of Science Is Bad, this trope occurs when science is portrayed as a force for good, and progress as an admirable goal for its own sake. Conversely, its absence, abuse, or suppression is portrayed as evil or detrimental to humanity. This viewpoint can take many forms \u0097 a Science Hero can use their skills to fight baddies, characters can teach the audience to appreciate science in everyday life, a setting's advancement and prosperity is credited to scientific discovery and engineering, or a team can use STEM to overcome problems of varying scales \u0097 from everyday nuisances to global catastrophe. These stories tend heavily towards the Enlightenment side of Romanticism Versus Enlightenment.\n\nThis is common in Post-Cyberpunk and Solar Punk; these genres answer Cyberpunk's (usual) message of Science Is Bad with more positive views on technology and industry. In the latter especially, a blend of nature and engineering results in an environmentally utopic future. Works can also take a more balanced stand \u0097 the abuse of science is bad, and it is best used as a force for good.\n\nHeroes of this story may be a Science Hero, The Smart Guy, or even a sympathetic Mad Scientist, while the villain may be an Evil Luddite. Compare In Harmony with Nature, which treats nature as \"good\", and with which this can overlap, especially if the focus is on life sciences. Contrast Science Is Bad, Science Is Wrong, Measuring the Marigolds.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceIsGood", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CivilizationBeyondEarth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DrStone", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/StellviaOfTheUniverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RaphaelSanzio", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/Aristotle", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/Plato", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SpiderMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/BigHero6", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/MeetTheRobinsons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/CloudyWithAChanceOfMeatballs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/BarbieInThePrincessAndThePauper", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheAmazingSpiderMan2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Avatar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BlackPanther2018", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheBeastFromTwentyThousandFathoms", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BrideOfFrankenstein", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Interstellar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ArtemisFowl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheSpaceTrilogy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheBigBangTheory", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Eureka", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheFlash2014", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Sliders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarTrek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheOriginalSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BillNyeTheScienceGuy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BillNyeSavesTheWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/TheyMightBeGiants", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Barbie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Toys/EverAfterHigh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Toys/MonsterHigh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LifeIsStrange", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LifeIsStrangeBeforeTheStorm", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManBattleNetwork", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManClassic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheOuterWorlds", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Xenoblade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Jem", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/JimmyNeutronBoyGenius", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheAdventuresOfJimmyNeutronBoyGenius"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InvertedTrope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceIsBad", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceHero", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceShow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RomanticismVersusEnlightenment", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.